columns: Standardized ring-width chronologies and sample depths for Sequoia sempervirens representing 11 living trees, 13 stumps, and two locations (Fort Ross State Historic Park, Gualala Redwood Timber Company). First row is location or tree ID. Second row is column header (# trees, # series, ring index). Each column corresponds with calendar years in the first column. Tree-level chronologies based on series dated with high crossdating confidence, detrended with 32-yr spline. Standard versions (STD) combined into location or regional chronologies via robust biweight mean with no further detrending. Gaps in chronologies exist at 1701−1706 for FRN4 and 1977−1979 for FRS3.
